##[ diary of the anti-"epidemic" ] the protection of horses under epidemic situation

Wechat, ynanth

Functional Introduction, welcome to pay attention to "anthropology of Dian" , every day there is new content, not to be missed. Monday: Theoretical and Methodological Studies; Wednesday: Historical Anthropological Studies; Thursday: Frontier Studies; Friday: Southwestern Studies; Saturday: Southeast Asian Studies; Tuesday Sunday, original column | says "human" using anthropological knowledge and experience, to reason or to tell a story.

[ author ] Ma Zhian, a native of Xiangcheng City, Henan Province (1995.8.1995) , is currently a graduate student in religious studies, Grade 2019, Yunnan University School of Ethnology and sociology.

On January 14,2020, on the 20th day of the 12th month, I was doing field work in the Najia camp. I received a message from my childhood friend on Wechat. He asked me if I would go home for the Spring Festival. If I did, I told him that he would also go back from Guangzhou. In this way, you'll have company during the holidays. It won't be so boring. So we agreed to go home for the Spring Festival this holiday.
After my field trip, I went straight home from school. Generally speaking, after the 20th of the 12th Lunar Month, it was the climax of the return of migrant workers to their hometowns. Of course, our village was no exception. Many people who had gone out to make a living were returning to the village one after another. After a year of desolation, the village slowly regained its vitality, in the past, the "Chess and card stall" and "Kan Kuo er qun" (Henan dialect, refers to a few people gathered together to chat) have attracted many "customers" .
On the 18th of January, the twenty-four of the 12th month, I remember this morning, I just woke up, i heard my mother say to my father, "you go to the East this morning and give incense to the old man. " I asked who died. My mother said, "the five old men of the East. ". Five old man is the consensus of our village good people, before he helps in the village every day Mat road, later the road hardened, he sat all day in the village entrance, to the traffic inflation. His funeral was attended by ten imams. Before the holidays, a classmate asked me to help her collect some information about ethnic minority funerals, which was a good opportunity. So I went with my dad to the old man's house. And recorded something.
On January 19, the 12th of the lunar month, I had planned to go to the old man's home for an interview with his family to find out the details of the funeral and the whole process. On second thought, his family had just suffered the loss of a loved one, and it wasn't a good time to go, so they decided to wait a few days.
At this time, a sudden epidemic interrupted my plan.
On January 22, the 12th of the lunar month, twenty-eight, a message about the closure of Wuhan was posted on our family's wechat group chat. At first, I didn't really care. Later, I heard that some villagers at home are also talking about the city of Wuhan, the spread of viruses and other topics, I just feel this matter is more serious. I went home to search the news, only to know that Wuhan has been all martial law, major pharmacies mask, disinfection drugs and so have been out of stock. At that time, the idea in my mind was that the virus is so serious, this year's Spring Festival plan is likely to blow up.
On January 23rd, the month of the Twelfth Month, twenty-nine, I saw news from my friends'circle early in the morning that hundreds of patients had been diagnosed with new pneumonia. The virus is not only transmissible from person to person, it also spreads very rapidly. I felt that things were not as simple as I thought, so I told my family to do a good job of protection and disinfection.
On January 24, the 30th of the 12th month, most villagers'awareness of protection is far from enough. All they know is to gather around and talk about what they've seen on the Internet, where they've been shut down, how many new cases have been confirmed, and even that the virus isn't coming to us, so there's no need to worry. But my uncle (village doctor) said: "This disease is not a simple virus infection, look at this situation and a few years ago SARS similar, even more serious than SARS. ". It's always good to be protected, he said.
January 25, the first day of the first month, today is the Spring Festival, early in the morning people will be in groups, to visit the elderly. Just as everyone was about to move around, the village committee received the notice of "starting the first-level emergency response for the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia in Henan Province" and received the order to close the village. After receiving the order, the village leadership immediately held a meeting to arrange the implementation plan. The leaders are divided into groups to take care of the activities of the returnees, especially those from Hubei and Wuhan. The party members in the village closed the road, all the paths leading into the village were blocked, only the main roads in and out of the village were left, and personnel were posted on duty to prevent all unsafe elements from leaving the village, such a simple mobile room, a table, a chair on the formation of the village epidemic command.
On January 26th, the second day of the first lunar month, according to tradition, today is the day to go home to one's mother's family. However, due to the closure of the village, all visits to relatives and friends are cancelled. This Day the village branch held an emergency branch conference, the meeting requested all Party members to play a model vanguard role, must all go to the village epidemic prevention front line, in this way, I participated in the "village protection action. ".

In order to accurately understand the situation of the village people returning home, the village decided to conduct statistics again, this time door-to-door investigation. As I was the youngest member of the Party in my village, I volunteered to take part in the house-to-house survey. The household survey was conducted for two days. During these two days, in addition to screening out people returning from other villages, our main purpose was to spread the knowledge of epidemic prevention among the villagers and advise people to stay indoors as much as possible. In the propaganda process, we are not immune to the opposition of some villagers, but in the face of such a severe situation, in order to ensure the safety of the villagers, we can only do our best to communicate with them.

On January 27th, the third day of the first lunar month, although the village has been closed for three days, villagers'awareness of protection is still far from strong enough, for example, some people still go out, and some villagers do not wear masks. At the checkpoint at the entrance to the village, we prepared some masks, distributed them to passers-by and gave them instructions not to go out during the outbreak.
(author himself)
From that day on, a set of epidemic prevention rules was established in the village. Party members and cadres took turns to guard the entrance of the village. Also from this day on, the village radio broadcast throughout the day during the epidemic prevention regulations. It was through the radio that the villagers learned of the severity of the disaster, and the number of people leaving the village has decreased considerably since about January 28. After checking the houses in the village, we found three people who had returned from Hubei Province. For these three people, we put them in isolation at home and arranged for a doctor to take their temperature. Not only that, the village also through the telephone, Wechat and other means of comfort and psychological counseling, with them through the isolation period, until they are safe.
On January 31, the seventh day of the first lunar month, people under the epidemic of panic, mobile phone Wechat, douyin become people's emotional communication tools and entertainment platform. As the weather was better today, the young people who had been at home for seven days could not stand the loneliness any longer. Many of them walked out of their homes and strolled along the country lanes. But at this time the epidemic is still very serious, which undoubtedly brought us on duty staff a series of workload, the village cadres immediately decided to let us go down to the village to "drive people. ". So, the village has another patrol, party members in addition to the village guard, but also in the village every day patrol, so day after day spent the first 14 days.
February 9th, the 16th day of the first lunar month. Today is the beginning of the second 14 days. We have orders from higher up. We need more protection. From this day on, the village is divided into regions, each cadre is responsible for a region of the villagers in the region to carry out knowledge of the epidemic. Checkpoints at the entrance of the village have also increased their night watches, requiring them to be on duty 24 hours a day. Meanwhile, people living in the urban area are also prohibited from returning to the village. All Trades, places of entertainment, places of religion except supermarkets and pharmacies are closed, and all materials need to be purchased by the village committee. Up to now, the protection work of our village is still going on very tensely.
The protection of our village is only a small microcosm of the great battle against the plague, which is fought all over the country. As the village radio said: "This is a Live and Let Die war. Either you kill the virus or the virus kills you. Win, the next year after the Spring Festival, lose, this year is your last Spring Festival. So everyone should stay at home consciously, do not go to cause trouble to the country, since can not be on the front line of Epidemic Prevention, then do a law-abiding backup force.
This winter vacation although I did not complete the plan to collect materials, although not and two years did not see the childhood outing, but I am fulfilling their own pledge to join the party.
In the face of the epidemic, we can not move, but wherever you are, please protect yourself. Together, we can win this pandemic!
